      • asString

        String asString()
        Coerces the value of the bound object to a display string.

        The implementation will incorporate the application textual convention and display hint (if available) of the corresponding MIB object definition.

        Specified by:
        asString in interface ObjectValue
        Returns:
        string representation of the bound object

      • toObject

        Object toObject()
        Gets the value of the object as one of the fundamental types of SMI.

        This method returns a value for each SMI type as follows:

        • OBJECT IDENTIFIER — int array of the OID components
        • OCTET STRING — byte array containing the object's octets
        • INTEGER — Long value of the object
        • NULL — null
        • IpAddress — byte array containing the address's octets
        • Counter — Long value of the object
        • Gauge — Long value of the object
        • TimeTicks — Long value of the object
        • Opaque — byte array containing the object's octets
        Specified by:
        toObject in interface ObjectValue
        Returns:

      • getIndexes

        Varbind[] getIndexes()
        Gets the bindings that represent the index values the bound value.
        Returns:
        if the bound value is a member of a conceptual table, the variable bindings representing the object's table index are returned; an empty array is returned for an object that is not a table member
